title: Lucky 7
overview:
Lucky 7
    
        Play Lucky 7 demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: All the colours of the rainbow and plenty of four leaf clovers fill this slot with fun for all. Unfortunately the price for playing is too high with an RTP of 93.05%.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Welcome to a world of luck.
Not only does Lucky Sevens sport lucky sevens by the score, it also focuses in on the four leaf clover. Oddly its obsession with clover, almost excludes the other forms of luck – like ladybirds and horseshoes – which are squeezed into the field full of clover, just for variety.
There is a background of clover to go with the theme and, one assumes because clover is associated with the Irish, also a rainbow with a pot of gold.
It is not a consistent theme, but its fun enough if you don’t think too hard about it.

media.caption: Simple win in Lucky 7 slot machine

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Part of the reason this slapdash, clover obsessed, theme works is that it is rendered rather well in the graphics department. It has a colourful and well drawn set of symbols, a set of simple but sparkly animations, and lots of varied movement to draw the eye along the animations.
The music on the other hand seems to have been added in as an afterthought, only playing while the reels spins and seeming to be cut off somewhat arbitrarily mid note when they stop. Luckily you can turn this off.

media.caption: Paytable of Lucky Rainbow bonus game

Gameplay.text:
The main gameplay is a simpe five reel slot. It has, unusually, eighteen winlines and no way to adjust the number of lines you play.
The pacing can be odd, but there are plenty of options in the software to speed up or slow down the reels and animations, and a fast spin option for the really impatient.

media.caption: Gameplay video featuring Lucky Rainbow bonus game

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
There are three special symbols to keep an eye out for. Unlike most games, in which the Wild symbol usually substitutes for any symbol, the Wild symbol in Lucky 7 only substitutes for sevens, in any colour. It also adds a multiplier of times two to any combo involving a "7" symbol in the main game.
The Colour Bonus symbol triggers the Colour Bonus game when you hit three of them anywhere in the rightmost three reels. By clicking on the bonus symbol you receive a randomised number of free spins and are assigned one "special colour".
During the free spins every clover in the special colour than lands wins you one times your initial bet.
If you hit three Lucky Rainbow symbols on the first three reels you enter the Lucky Rainbow bonus game. In this bonus you receive seven free spins and the symbols on the reels are replaced by new symbols in the colours of the rainbow plus silver.
During the Lucky Rainbow bonus any combo using a Wild symbol gains a multiplier of three times any winning combo of the silver, orange and yellow symbols.

media.caption: Win in the Lucky Rainbow bonus game
Wild symbol awards a winning only in combination with symbols 7

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
This slot has an insanely low return to player of 93.05%, which is an instant disqulification. Anything under 96% is poor, 93% is practically robbery.
By combining coin values and "steps", which are little more than a multiplier for both bet and payouts, the bet per spin can range from €/£/$0.18 at the minimum up to a highest bet per spin of €/£/$180.00.
There is no available volatility information on this slot. However, on the basis of how frequently it pays out it feels like it has low to medium volatility.

media.caption: Base game paytable of Lucky 7 slot

Conclusion.text:
Lucky Sevens has a lot going for it: fun bonus games, a vibrant and exciting visual style, and enough four leaved clovers to feed the luckiest cow ever.
However, it is let down massively by the very low return to player and the strange betting system created by Espresso.
We do not recommend Lucky 7.

title: Alice In Wonderland
overview:
Alice In Wonderland
    
        Play Alice In Wonderland demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Might be best not to follow the rabbit down this particular hole. A low volatility and middling RTP (96.06%) means this slot is not our cup of tea.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Alice in Wonderland is perhaps the most prolifically adapted book in all of slot history. In BF Games’s adaptation – simply entitled Alice in Wonderland – the style is heavily art nouveau, though it still borrows some of its tone from the famous original illustrations of the book by John Tenniel.
Present, as you might expect, are the usual suspects: Alice and her headband, the White Rabbit with his watch, the Mad Hatter, the Cheshire Cat.
They didn’t stretch to the Queen of Hearts, otherwise they would have won full bingo for things people know about Alice In Wonderland if they had never read the book as a child.
It’s a classic theme dealt with in a classic manner.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are excellent. However, the slot doesn’t deal very well with scaling. Full screened on a computer it looks clean and crisp but on a phone or a small browser window the visuals become pixelated and the font sizes overly small.
Once the game is full screen though, the game is pretty enough with a lovely watercolour style to the imagery and backgrounds.
The animations are simple but work well, with magical flourishes here and there. The music is a pleasant ambient track that adds to the atmosphere of, well, wonder. But it manages to do so without being invasive.

media.caption: Win in the Alice in Wonderland slot machine

Gameplay.text:
Alice in Wonderland is a five reel slot sporting three rows and an any way wins system with 243 ways to win. The any way wins system means that winning combinations are made by the same symbols in adjacent reels so long as they run left to right starting from reel one.
There is a gamble feature for those who want a little more variance. As with many games, it is a simple game where the player must pick the colour of the next card off an infinite deck. The odds are 2:1 on each bet.
The bonus is a free spin bonus (details below).

media.caption: Alice in Wonderland offers the option of a gamble feature
Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol.
Hitting three or more Scatter symbols on one spin triggers ten free spins with a randomly chosen expanding symbol. These free spins can be retriggered.
During the free spins, Wild symbols come in stacks of three and appear on reels two to five. As a result, it is possible to land twelve of these symbols at once.
In the base game, the Drink symbol is stacked and plays as both a Wild and as a regular symbol.

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.06%, spot on our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.25 up to a maximum of $/£/€200.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is low, which makes it a very poor match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility.

media.caption: High paying symbols in the Alice in Wonderland slot machine

Conclusion.text:
Alice in Wonderland is a pretty slot, but lacks substance.
While the design and soundtrack are excellent, the average RTP coupled with low volatility makes this slot a poor match for our strategies.
In almost all other ways, this slot is perfectly fine. It doesn’t thrill the player, but nor does it make any huge missteps. If the low variance isn’t a dealbreaker for you, this game will probably be satisfactory, if unexciting.

about_game: The dark and pagan monoliths of Asgardian Stones make for an atmospheric and attractive slot. But pretty average features and volatility that is too low undercut an otherwise excellent product.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Plenty of slot machines have tackled the world of the Vikings and the myths of the Norse Gods, but few approach from the angle Asgardian Stones takes. Here the star of the show are not the characters of that world, but its relics.
In place of gods and warriors, Asgardian Stones has a pile of rune marked carven faces, eerie caves and brooding choral soundtrack.

Gameplay.text:
Although Asgardian Stones is technically a five reel slot, rather than spinning reels the symbols fall into place as blocks. The twenty winlines are then checked and any blocks that are part of a win are destroyed triggering an ‘avalanche’. New stones fall to take the place of the old and these stones rechecked for wins. The spin ends when there are no further avalanche wins.
Colossal symbols are part of how this work, with each symbol appearing as one (except the Wild and Bonus symbols). These Colossal symbols are either two by two or three by three sized symbols. The entire Colossal symbol is destroyed even if only part of it is used in a winning combination.
If there are any empty spaces under a Colossal symbol (as there might be once the winning lines have been removed from the spin), then all the symbols under the Colossal symbol are destroyed until it is resting on no empty spaces.
Each time it falls and destroys a symbol the multiplier is bumped up by one. The maximum multiplier you can win from this feature is four times your winnings.

When the wheel stops it awards either free spins or a payout of coins. There is a maximum coin payout of 36 times the bet per spin.
If the block covers three rows, you win three prizes off the wheel and so on down to one if the block rests on the top row.
During the free spins, a Colossal Wild is added which breaks up into nine single Wild blocks. This allows for more wins as these blocks can then be part of avalanche wins.

media.caption: The bonus wheel with a chance of winning up to 15 free spins

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player for Asgardian Stones is 96.31% which is not too bad when compared to the trends in the industry.
The slot is moderately volatile. We prefer high volatility slots.
The site we tested allowed a minimum bet of £/$/€0.20 as you must play all twenty winlines. The maximum bet was £/$/€200 per spin.

media.caption: Asgardian Stones - Top symbols paytable

Conclusion.text:
A beautiful slot machine with great visuals and some lovely design elements. The features are solid and the RTP decent. However, we would normally look for higher volatility in a slot we would recommend.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Lights is an odd slot, with a visual theme based around Chinese lanterns and the various styles they come in. The background to the slot is a gorgeous, almost magical landscape, while the symbols are various lanterns and the usual ace to ten symbols.
As themes go it might not seem to be all that rich visually, but by combining the lanterns with drifting, firefly-like lights the slot does manage to create a pleasing aesthetic that can be enjoyed by most players.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The key way in which the odd theme sells itself is in the graphics. They are charming and pretty, with the firefly patterns adding a magical element to the twilight glow of the lamps.
The musical accompaniment is not great but if it could be muted it would allow the well chosen sound effects to shine.

Gameplay.text:

Gameplay video featuring 10 free spins bonus

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
Wilds play as any symbol except for Scatters. Floating Wilds land at random on top of another symbol.
Hitting three or more Scatters triggers the free spin bonus. Three Scatters gets you ten free spins, four gets you twenty, five will win you the biggest prize of thirty free spins.
During free spins additional value is added by an increase in the number of floating Wilds which are now between three and six in number every spin.

Gameplay.text:

title: Twin Spin Deluxe
overview:
Twin Spin Deluxe
    
        Play Twin Spin Deluxe demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Twin Spin Deluxe is a neon and disco take on a classic formula with the added twist of twinned reels and win clusters. Nice design, but it could use some more features and more volatility in our book.

Theme and Storyline.text:
There is a large section of the slot machine world given over to games that are based on the old one-armed bandit style fruit machine. These old machines, with their single win lines and mechanical reels, created all the main images of slot machines and fixed them in our minds. The one-armed bandit is where the symbols for lucky 7s, cherries, lemons, the BAR symbol and golden bells came into existence.
The new machines take this aesthetic and normally boil down the wide variety of gameplay modes in online slots to something much simpler. They strip out side games, bonuses, multiple winlines and are often played on the same three by three reels as a mechanical fruit machine.
Twin Spins is part of this old style family and uses the same theme, but takes a different tack when it comes to how it approaches it.

media.caption: Twin Spin Deluxe - no winlines, just clustered symbols

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
For a start there is nothing classic about the graphics. Instead, the background is a computer generated set of 3-D disco floor lights. The symbols are drawn in as neon lights and the music is a pulsing pseudo-disco dance track.
The modernised graphics and sound do work pretty well, with the classic symbols rendered in new fangled ways and the animations slick enough to justify their garishness.
The design shouldn’t work, but it does and somehow manages to still be in the spirit of simplicity that is part of this style of game.

Gameplay.text:
The gameplay also deviates the idea of simple, old style games but still retains that spirit of simplicity. There are no bonus features, no Wilds or Scatters, but in place of winlines Twin Spin Deluxe pays out on clusters of symbols. Nine or more symbols touching each other vertically or horizontally (not diagonally) will pay out.
One additional twist is the Twin Spins of the title in which at least two adjacent reels, randomly chosen each spin, are lined up with identical symbols on each. These can expand to fill any number of reels between two and six.
All this plays out on a six by five grid.

media.caption: At least 2 reels are identical in every spin
Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text: There are no bonuses, wilds, or free spins in Twin Spin Deluxe.

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
Twin Spin Deluxe has a respectable return to player of 96.61%. While not the highest, it is a little higher than our yardstick of around 96%. This middling return to player is coupled with a middling level of variance, which is too low for us to recommend this slot.
The site we tested allowed bets ranging from £/$/€0.10 to £/$/€100.00 per spin.

media.caption: Twin Spin Deluxe paytable - cluster of 9 to 30 symbols

Conclusion.text: Twin Spin Deluxe as a design object is excellent, it is shark like in its simplicity and elegance.

title: Double Stacks
overview:
Double Stacks
    
        Play Double Stacks demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Double the stacks, double the fun? Not so much in this very average fruit machine style slot machine with a twist.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Double Stacks has a retro one-armed bandit feel. The typical fruit machine symbols are all here, Diamonds, Bars, Sevens, Bells and so on.
However, where many slot machines that adopt this theme do so to evoke a kind of old style one winline simplicity, Double Stacks comes with a bunch of gameplay twists and bonuses (see below for details).
For a game that has taken this well-worn theme for its design, it doesn’t do much to stand out.

media.caption: NetEnt's take on a classic fruit slot with a twist

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text: The symbols are pretty bland, if competently designed, and don’t do much to draw the player in. But the jazzy background they are contrasted against is pretty stylish and the animations are done with great flare and a have a nice 3D shine on them.

Gameplay.text:
Double Stacks is a ten winline slot machine played on a five-by-three grid.
The key twist on gameplay is the Double Stack of the game’s title, wherein the four highest paying symbols appear stacked in the main game. This allows you to make large combination wins by landing multiple stacks of the same symbol. The highest payout is for filling the entire screen with the diamond symbol.
The double stack is triggered when you fill a reel with one symbol, that symbol then changes to a double stack symbol and counts as two symbols for the purpose of calculating winnings.
The maximum payouts for these wins is written across the top of the screen.

media.caption: Winning is easy in Double Stacks slot
Gameplay video featuring free spins bonus

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol (the star with Wild written on it) plays as any symbol except for the Scatter symbol.
If you hit three or more Scatter symbols the Free Spin bonus is triggered. If you hit three Scatters you get five free spins,or four Scatters you get fifteen and five Scatters grant you thirty spins.
You can Retrigger spins by hitting two or more Scatters with two Scatters earning you two extra respins.
During Free Spins the Wilds can also appear in stacks.

media.alt: Double Stacks stacked wilds in free spins
media.caption: Win big with stacked wilds in the bonus game

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player is 96.10%. This is neither good nor bad, but more or less what we expect from the industry.
The site we tested allowed a rand of bets per spin that ranged from £/$/€0.10 up to £/$/€200.00. That is a good spread that will please most bankroll sizes.
Double Stacks has its volatility rated as medium by various online sources. We prefer high volatility games as they fit with our preferred strategies.

media.caption: Fairly easy to collect huge wins with free spins bonus

Conclusion.text:
NetEnt's Double Stacks is an old style fruit machine stacked with a twist.
Whether or not the double stacks are enough to make Double Stacks stand out is doubtful, but what really puts paid to any hope of a recommendation is the bog standard return to player and medium volatility neither of which is high enough to really tempt us into playing.

title: Ace Ventura Pet Detective
overview:
Ace Ventura Pet Detective
    
        Play Ace Ventura Pet Detective demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Ace Ventura Pet Detective serves up nostalgia and good bonuses but is let down by a poor RTP and disappointing winning potential.

Theme and Style.text: Ace Ventura Pet Detective is a movie-themed slot designed and developed by Atlantic Digital. The slot is based on the popular 1990s movies of the same name.

media.alt: Ace Ventura Pet Detective slot win
media.caption: Win in the Ace Ventura Pet Detective slot

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Atlantic Digital has clearly sought permission to use the Ace Ventura Pet Detective intellectual property, with fans of the movie being treated to a huge blast from the past when they load the game.
The reels are set in front of a popular location from the movie, while the symbols consist of Jim Carrey, the actor who played Ace Ventura Pet Detective, in various situations. Other popular items from the movie make an appearance as the remaining higher-paying symbols.
Ace Ventura Pet Detective is brought to life with some hilarious animations and film sequences, while an upbeat soundtrack and sound effects from the movie help keep the tempo high.

media.alt: Ace Ventura Pet Detective slot - Jackpot Wheel
media.caption: Jackpot Wheel feature of the game

Gameplay.text:
Ace Ventura might be a whacky guy, but there is nothing wild about the base game action here. The slot uses a conventional 5x3 game grid, with 20 active paylines on each spin. Players will score a win if they land three or more matching symbols along a payline, starting on the leftmost reel.
The control panel for the slot is located on the right-hand side of the grid. Here, you will find the paytable, the stake adjustment options, and the autoplay feature.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
Like other movie titles such as The Goonies and Ted from Blueprint Gaming, Ace Ventura Pet Detective is packed with bonus features.
Landing three Scatters on the middle three reels launches the Trigger & Collect Free Spins bonus. During the round, Wilds have a Multiplier attached to them that is applied to any wins it is involved in. Multipliers on a single line are added together.
The slot also follows in the footpath of popular games like Big Bass Bonanza and uses a collection mechanic. During the Free Spins, Snowflake the Dolphin will land, displaying cash values. These are collected if they land at the same time as a Wild.
Landing three or more Mini Wheel Scatters launches the Mini Wheel bonus. All three wheels will spin and their prizes are multiplied together and paid out. You can also win one of four jackpots on the wheel.
You can also win a Jackpot by landing three, four, or five of the Jackpot Scatter symbols. These reward the Mini, Minor, or Major Jackpots, respectively.
Players can skip the queue by using the Buy Bonus feature to launch the Free Spins round.

media.alt: Ace Ventura Pet Detective slot - Detect & Collect spins
media.caption: Free Spins bonus with the Detect and Collect feature

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
In the demo provided, the Ace Ventura Pet Detective slot’s RTP comes in at 93.90%, which is significantly below the industry average according to the criteria set out in our slot strategy guide. However, there are versions on the market with a higher RTP, so we recommend checking to see which version you are playing, with some offering significantly higher. The highest version available is 96.18%.
The maximum win is 3,200x the player’s stake, while the game has been given a medium volatility rating.

media.alt: Ace Ventura Pet Detective - High paying symbols
media.caption: Paytable for the high paying symbols of the game

Conclusion.text: Atlantic Digital pulls on the nostalgia strings with Ace Ventura Pet Detective. A fun design and bonuses will pull players in and are selling points. However, we recommend approaching with caution and checking the RTP before you play. The version at 93.90% should be avoided, so if you want to play, look for one of the higher models on the market.

title: Archer
overview:
Archer
    
        Play Archer demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Archer has a face as pretty as Maid Marion but a heart as black as the Sheriff of Nottingham. The low RTP of 94.99% and medium volatility should warn you away from these woods.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Archer is a slot that has clearly been built around the iconography of Robin Hood, but has leaned away from being direct about it in the title.
Given how familiar we all are with the Robin Hood mythos, it is no bad thing that this slot takes a different tack. Making what was old, new again.
Perhaps it was for the same reason their Robin Hood looks rather old, and their Friar Tuck and Guy Gisborne look eerily like brothers. The strange character designs notwithstanding, Archer does a nice take on the story with a well-built world for the characters to inhabit and plenty of medieval style in the designs.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Archer’s graphics are well designed, offering a neat new take on the familiar characters. There is some pixelation in the imagery that gives the whole thing the feel of late-90s point and click adventures.
The animations are a little basic. And really just highlight the few things that are necessary to make wins clear and to sell the player on the idea that there really are reels spinning.
There is also a musical track that plays as part of the spin sounds and does a good job of echoing the musical score of those technicolour classics put out by Hollywood in the mid-20th Century.

media.caption: 5 of a kind win with Expand and Split feature

Gameplay.text:
Archer is on the face of it a simple five reel slot with three rows and an any way wins system.
However, it sports a neat little gameplay feature in the base game called Expand and Split. Random cells on the reels have an arrow border. When these symbols are part of a winning combo and a Scatter is present on the reels, they expand to fill their entire row.
However, instead of replacing the other symbols on the reel, those other symbols split and become both their original symbol and the expanded one.

media.alt: Archer slot - wild symbols big win
media.caption: Big win with the Expand and Split feature and the Wild symbol combination

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol and appears on reels two, three and four.
Three or more Scatter symbols anywhere on the reels trigger a Free Spin bonus in which the player starts with seven free spins. They also pay out twice the player’s bet per spin for three Scatters, and ten and fifty times the player’s bet for four and five Scatters respectively.
During the free spins, the Expand and Split feature is triggered for all symbols with an arrow border if they are part of a winning combination. This is different from the base game, where the Expand and Split feature is triggered only when a Scatter is also present.
Free Spins can be retriggered with no upper limit to the total number of Free Spins.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 94.99%, a little over a percentage point below our yardstick for average of roughly 96%. This counts badly against the game, especially as the volatility is only medium.
Medium volatility makes this slot a poor match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility. This could be made up for by a generous RTP, but this slot opts to steal from the rich, without giving to the poor.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.25 up to a maximum of $/£/€1,250.00 per spin.

media.caption: Paytable for the Archer slot machine

Conclusion.text:
Archer is a fun, immersive Robin Hood-themed slot with some nice little visual quirks that keep it fresh.
However, once the surface is scratched, the game is rather dull. The Expand and Split feature by itself is interesting, but does not manage to work with the other features to create something worth playing.
On top of this the poor RTP means the game is expensive to play, and the medium volatility won’t work as well with our slot strategies as higher volatility games.

title: Gladiator Jackpot
overview:
Gladiator Jackpot
    
        Play Gladiator Jackpot demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Fans of the movie will be disappointed, fans of slots even more so. This slot’s medium volatility and 94.09% gets a thumbs down from us.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Gladiator Jackpot is a movie themed slot which follows the plot of the classic Ridley Scott movie Gladiator.
Unfortunately, getting the trademark didn’t give them the rights to Russell Crowe’s likeness, so the main character does not appear anywhere in the game.
One additional strangeness about this slot is the fact that the word "colosseum" is spelled throughout as "coliseum", a medieval alternative spelling that hasn’t been widely used for six hundred years.
There are plenty of Rome themed slots that feel closer in tone to the movie than this one. If you want a slot that captures the feel of that film, play one of them.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Despite having movie studio approval the final product is a bit rickety. Adjusting screen size away from the scale the designers built it results in ugly pixelation.
The choice of character photos are uninspiring and the animations simple involve swapping in a new picture and zooming in and out.
There is no backing music. A massive oversight given the influence the original Hans Zimmer soundtrack had. Even a faded imitation would have been better than the generic win and spin sounds the makers selected.
Overall, the design of this slot is enormously disappointing for fans of either slot machines, or the movie Gladiator.

media.caption: Win in the Gladiator Jackpot slot

Gameplay.text:
The base game is a basic five reel slot with three rows. The game has twenty-five win lines, which are adjustable.
There is no gamble feature. Though it has two bonus games, these do not do much for the pacing or excitement of a game that seems to have been worked on with very limited effort.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol.
Three or more Wild symbols landing on one spin trigger the Gladiator Jackpot Bonus. This allows the player a spin on special reels. There are nine spots on a grid, each spot gets one of three Helmet symbols in either Gold, Silver, or Bronze. The metal corresponds to a particular multiplier. The player wins the total value of all nine Helmets. If all nine are Gold Helmets, then the player wins the progressive jackpot (unless the bonus was triggered during a free spin).
Three or more Scatter symbols trigger the Coliseum Bonus. This is a Free Spin bonus, with a picking game to randomise the number of free spins, the multiplier for those spins, and reels with additional scatter and wild symbols.

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 94.09%. This is much too low. We use a yardstick for average of roughly 96%, and coming in two percentage points is a black mark which no slot is good enough to overcome. That sound you hear is our recommendation being thrown to the lions.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.01 up to a maximum of $/£/€25.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is medium. That would make it a poor match for our preferred slot machine strategies even if the RTP weren’t painfully low.

media.caption: High paying symbols of the Gladiator Jackpot slot machine

Conclusion.text:
After one recovers from the shock of a licensed slot machine game without Russell Crowe, Hans Zimmer, or tigers, one can be shocked all over again by how lazy the design of this slot is.
The user interface is ugly, the soundtrack is not very immersive, and the RTP is insanely low.
There isn’t a single redeeming feature to this tired and lazy slot. Two thumbs down.

title: Great Blue
overview:
Great Blue
    
        Play Great Blue demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: High volatility and a reasonable RTP are the main selling points for this charming if basic undersea themed slot.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Great Blue takes its players down beneath the ocean in a fun cartoon rendering of the briny deep. Play with orcas and great whites, seahorses and angel fish, as you try to hunt down the pearls that will trigger the bonus for a big haul of undersea treasures.
The reels are bursting with sea life with each creature as full of character as they are of micro-plastic pollution.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The visuals are charming, with each creature rendered in a style that feels just right for the particular world that this slot is trying to create.
The animations let the side down a bit, failing to add much in the way of atmosphere and looking a little rushed to boot. It is not off-putting, but more effort could have been spent in this department.
The sounds are where the slot really lets the side down. The spin sounds are a short steel band calypso, but it just feels generic and no other sounds or background music have been added to help sell the theme to the player.

media.caption: Win in the Great Blue slot machine

Gameplay.text:
Great Blue’s gameplay is taken entirely from the slot machine 101 playbook. A solid but unimaginative combo of a five by three slot with twenty-five win lines, and a Free Spin bonus.
There is no gamble feature, and no additional bonuses to keep things varied.
What gameplay features it does have are well paced and well made, so this slot will work for most players.

media.caption: Gameplay video featuring free spins bonus

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol. Any wins that include a Wild have a times two multiplier added to them.
The Scatter symbol pays out for two or more symbols anywhere on the reels. Three or more Scatters will also trigger a Free Spin bonus.
The Free Spin bonus starts with a times two multiplier and eight free spins. The player then picks five shells with random numbers of additional spins and multipliers, allowing them to get up to thirty-three free spins and a times fifteen multiplier.
Free Spins can be retriggered.

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.03%, pretty much spot on our yardstick for an average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.25 up to a maximum of $/£/€50.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is high, which makes it an excellent match for our preferred slot machine strategies. We like to target the highest possible volatility.

media.caption: Full paytable of the Great Blue slot machine

Conclusion.text:
Great Blue has plenty of charm, high volatility, and an average RTP. That all works in its favour, though it is a little over-simple in its gameplay and lacks the atmosphere that a more rigorous set of sounds and animations would make.
Overall this one gets a mild recommendation from us, though we can easily imagine that for the right player it could be a niche favourite.

title: Highway Kings
overview:
Highway Kings
    
        Play Highway Kings demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Simple to play and simpler to look at, Highway Kings hides a lorry load of RTP and volatility.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Highway Kings is set among the world of long distance truckers. At the top of the screen are a pair of the enormous Peterbilts that haul eighteen-wheelers along Route 66 in an endless cycle of mobile, high-speed capitalism. That can be a perfect metaphor for the American dream, and in some ways for the slot industry.
There’s not much in the way of story to accompany the range of piston heads, tyres, fluffy dice, and spark plugs. But the theme is solidly presented and the iconic lorries make for striking visuals.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Those visuals could be executed better. With the exception of the trucks themselves, the symbols feel a little under designed. The artwork is clear enough, but has a slightly cheap and cheerful look to it.
The background is a simple blue gradient, and doesn’t add very much. The animations are as basic as they come. One for the reel, and blinking lines to indicate wins.
Sound gets a little more effort. There are metallic spin sounds and a horn which honks when a winning combination lands. These sound effects generate some atmosphere, but without music or ambient sound to back them up, they feel tinny and isolated.

media.alt: Highway Kings & 5 of a kind win
media.caption: 5 of a kind win in the Highway Kings slot machine

Gameplay.text:
To go with its simple visuals, Highway Kings offers similarly stripped down gameplay. A basic five reel slot, with three rows and one to nine win lines that pay both from left and right.
It comes without a gamble feature or bonuses.
This is truly the minimalist experience.

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol. Any win containing a Wild has a multiplier of x2 applied to it.
There are no Free Spins or Bonuses in this game.

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 97.06%, one full percentage point above our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.01 up to a maximum of $/£/€9.00 per spin. This favours lower stakes players. Anyone looking for higher limits might have to shop around to find a casino that offers them.
The volatility of this game is high. Combining this with the high RTP, this slot is a brilliant match for our preferred slot strategies. Our slot machine strategies tend to target the highest possible volatility.

media.alt: Highway Kings top paying symbols paytable
media.caption: Paytable for most valuable symbols of the game

Conclusion.text:
A solid, simple slot with enough atmospheric details to get away with so simple a design.
Both visuals and gameplay are simple. There are no bonuses or other extras in play. Instead the player just spins and either wins or loses. This kind of pure experience will only appeal to certain kinds of players.
If it does appeal to you, we have additional good news. The RTP is nice and high (97.09%) and the volatility is through the roof. Put together that makes this slot a lovely match for our preferred strategies.
We highly recommend this slot.

title: King Kong
overview:
King Kong
    
        Play King Kong demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Hunting King Kong through the jungle of Skull Island and the urban jungle of New York has never been so much fun. With some nice bonus features and clean design, King Kong is a solid slot. It is let down somewhat by the drab imagery and dull core gameplay.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Welcome to Skull Island, where the water is warm but the locals are decidedly unfriendly.
Based on Peter Jackson’s epic and under-rated remake of the 1930s classic King Kong, this slot takes you from Skull Island to the Island of Manhattan in your pursuit of, and then your attempt to recapture, the mighty Kong – and along the way, hopefully, haul in a little coin.
Big blockbuster movies are good source material for slots, and the iconography of King Kong with its jungle settings, wild beasts and iconic biplane vs beast finale provide plenty of imagery to work with.

media.alt: King Kong's movie stars as high symbols
media.caption: King Kong's movie stars (Naomi Watts, Adrien Brody, Jack Black) act as the highest symbols in this slot machine

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Which is why it is odd that the slot is so visually lacklustre.
The animation is shiny and smooth, and the soundtrack understated and immersive (just drums when you spin and a little musical sting when you win).
But for some reason, with the full range of Skull Island’s flora and fauna to choose from the slot designers have opted to leave out the giant spiders and T-rexes from the images. They even ignore the fearsome indigenous people whose painted faces and piercings are the kind of striking visuals a slot needs.
Instead, the symbols are just a few of the main cast (Adrian Brody, Naomi Watts and Jack Black) some archaeological looking Ace to Ten symbols and then, of course, King himself who appears rarely in the role of a Wild symbol.

Gameplay.text:
The gameplay is pretty straightforward stuff. King Kong is a 20 win-line five reel slot.
Its main innovation is to have two modes in which the setting changes. When you hit the Skull Island bonus (more on the bonus systems below) in the jungle setting and win a cash prize the background changes to the city and you continue playing in the new City Mode.
City Mode doesn’t change the payouts but it does change the bonus game to the Tower bonus. Overall the gameplay shows little imagination and underuses the Theme they chose.

media.caption: City mode in King Kong slot
Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
Each of the modes (Jungle and City) have slightly different twists on the two bonus modes.
Kong’s face acts as a Wild symbol and also triggers a respin feature. In Jungle mode, you get three free spins.
During the Jungle mode respin feature, the game locks any Wild symbols in place for any subsequent spins. While the City mode respin feature makes whole columns wild for each of the free respins (1+5 in respin one, 2+4 in respin two, and 1+3+5 in respin three).
There is also a Scatter symbol the Kong 8th Wonder of the World symbol. Hit three or more of these on a spin and you trigger a Bonus game.
During the Jungle phase, this triggers a bonus game in which you pick locations and match three creatures to win prizes.
While during the city phase, hitting three or more Scatters in City mode will launch the Tower Bonus game in which you win random prizes based on which of three planes you knock down as Kong.
When you play a Bonus game, the setting automatically flips back to the previous mode.
You always start the game in Jungle mode.

media.alt: King Kong jungle mode bonus game
media.caption: King Kong's jungle mode bonus game

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
With a return of 95.50%, King Kong has a pretty standard payout. It is slightly at the lower end of what we estimate the average payout to be for slots like this, but is certainly not bad.
It is a relatively high-variance slot with regular very large payouts coming along very rarely. But being well worth it when they do.
It does allow you to control that variance a fair bit with the number of winlines. By allowing you any number between 1 and 20 winlines you can manipulate both your bet sizes and variance to a very granular level.
The site we tested allowed between €/£/$0.01 and €/£/$20.00, this doesn’t cater much for big spenders but different sites may give you a higher payout options.

media.caption: You can select between 1 and 20 winlines
Full paytable of the King Kong movie slot machine

Conclusion.text:
While King Kong fails to do all it could with its chosen setting, the gameplay is ultimately quite fun.
But only if you can stick with it long enough to hit the bonus features which add a pleasant twist to an otherwise very slick, but very conventional slot machine.

title: Vikings Fortune
overview:
Vikings Fortune
    
        Play Vikings Fortune demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: While Vikings Fortune is a winner at the level of its visual design and the programming of its gameplay, it fails to win us over when it comes to the low return to player and volatility.

Theme and Storyline.text: Viking’s Fortune takes you across the North Sea to a Viking settlement on the Danish coast. The setting is the wild North and the characters that populate the slot range from Odin’s raven to Loki’s wolf with a few blonde haired and blue eyed Scandies inbetween.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are as well drawn as you would expect from Playson, but with the added bonus of feeling alive and part of a unique world.
The music is a reasonably innocuous track with a pleasant early-medieval tone that sets the scene beautifully and does not get on the players nerves too quickly.
The animations are simple but work well. On the whole this is a well designed slot.

Gameplay.text:
Viking’s Fortune is a five reel slot, with three rows, and twenty-five win lines.
There are also two bonuses: Free Spins and the Bonus Game (details below). There are also three progressive jackpots which can be triggered through the Bonus Game.
This is plenty of features to keep a distractible player engaged.

media.caption: Gameplay video featuring Bonus Game

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter and Bonus symbols, and pays out the same as the highest value symbol for three or more on a win line.
The Scatter appears only on reels one, three, and five. If you hit one symbol on each of these reels, you win five times your bet and trigger the Free Spins game.
The Free Spins bonus starts with eight free spins. During the Free Spins, the high value and Bonus symbols can appear as large 2 x 2 or 3 x 3 "Colossal" symbols.
Not only can the Free Spins bonus be retriggered if you hit three or more Scatters during the Free Spins, but you can also trigger the Bonus Game bonus. If this happens, you play out the retriggered free spins or Bonus Game and then return to the initial Free Spins bonus.
Bonus symbols have a value on them of between x1 and x24 your bet per spin. If you hit five or more Bonus symbols anywhere on the reels during one spin, then the Bonus Game will be triggered. The Bonus symbols from the triggering spin will log in place and a spin counter will be set at three spins.
During the Bonus Game all Bonus symbols are locked in place from spin to spin. Hitting a new Bonus symbol on a spin resets the spin counter to three. When the counter reaches zero, the value on all the Bonus symbols are added up and the player wins that amount.
The Bonus Game can also trigger one of the three progressive jackpots: the Mini, Major or Grand jackpots.
The Mini and Major jackpots are triggered if the Mini or Major Bonus symbol lands during the Bonus Game. The Grand Jackpot is triggered if during a Bonus Game the player fills all fifteen cells on the reels.

media.caption: Hitting at least 5 bonus symbols award the Bonus Game
Last respin in the Bonus Game feature
Paytable for standard symbols

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 95.20%. We tend to use 96% as a rough yardstick, and this slot falls well below that.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.25 up to a maximum of $/£/€100.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is low, which makes it a terrible match for our preferred slot machine strategies which tend to rely on the highest possible volatility.

Our preference is for the highest variance possible to fit with our preferred strategies. The volatility of The Dalai Panda is at the top end of medium, almost in the high zone, and so is just high enough to squeak a recommendation though we would hope for a higher RTP to make up for this.

overview:

about_game: Visually hideous, this game has a high vig and dull gameplay that, unfortunately, is not made up for by the decent volatility and enticing bonuses.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Who doesn’t like cats? They are cute, fluffy pest control machines. Maybe they can be a little distant, a little cruel, but we like it when someone plays hard to get.
Unfortunately, Ainsworth's Pussy Cat features very little of our furry friends, instead opting for cat toys and comic sans ten to queen symbols.
As far as universally loveable themes, that seems like a missed opportunity.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
In fact, the lack of cats is not the only missed opportunity. In making the various visual decisions that need to be made when building a slot machine Ainsworth – the Australian based slot maker that made Pussy Cat – seems to have made all the wrong decisions.
The game is, simply put, hideous to look at. The imagery is rendered in cheaply drawn icons and ugly colours. The whole thing looks like it was rendered in Microsoft Paint circa 1999, not a release from early 2019 as it, surprisingly, is in fact.
The sound design is the only place they made the right choice, eschewing a musical accompaniment and keeping win chimes and reel noises to the most bog standard specifications possible.

Gameplay.text:
The game is a 25 win line slot with a standard five by three grid. The main variation in the gameplay comes from the somewhat convoluted selection of Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins covered below.
The gameplay is pretty typical and the additional variations manage to do nothing to elevate the game beyond complete boredom.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wilds appear on reels 2,3 and 4 and substitute for all other symbols except the Scatter.
The Scatter pays out from any position (2x your bet for 3 symbols, 20x for 4, and 50x for 5) and triggers a respin if you hit exactly two of them. During the respin the reels with a Scatter on them are held in place. Three or more Scatters triggers the Free Spins bonus.
During the Free Spins bonus there are a number of changes to the reels: a Silver Wild is added to reels 2, 3, and 4 in addition to the regular Wild; both Wilds and Silver Wilds are each assigned a random multiplier between one and six times; a new paytable is in effect; and the Grand, Major, Minor, and Mini Bonuses are brought online.
The Silver Wilds play just like regular Wilds but if you land both a Wild and a Silver Wild on one winline your win is multiplied by the total of the two multipliers on the Wild and Silver Wild symbol involved.
If a reel is covered by three Wilds, the player also wins one of either the Grand, Major, Minor, or Mini Bonuses.

media.caption: Big win in the Pussy Cat slot machine

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
With variance at the high end of medium, so we can give this a mild recommendation on this aspect of the slot. Overall though we would suggest avoiding this slot in favour of something with a little more volatility.
The return to player on this game is a dismally low 94.16%, which is much too low at almost 2% lower than our estimated average of 96%.
The site we tested offered a bet size ranging from a minimum bet per spin of £/$/€1.00 to a maximum bet per spin of £/$/€40.00. This is an oddly low range of bets.

media.alt: Pussy Cat slot top symbols paytable
media.caption: Top symbols paytable for Pussy Cat slot

Conclusion.text:
This is an ugly game, with a hideously low return to player. Together these would normally be enough to eliminate any possibility of a recommendation.
The only redeeming feature is the high(ish) volatility and, in particular, the jackpot style Grand and Major bonuses.

Much of the disappointment in this theme comes from the fact that the slot is badly designed. While not as ugly as some of Ainsworth’s output, Enchanted Eyes is rather bland to look at. There is no background music to speak of, which is probably a blessing if the rest of the sound design is anything to go by.

media.caption: Win in the Enchanted Eyes slot machine

Gameplay.text: The gameplay is the 25 win line, five by three slot machine that all Ainsworth slots seem to be built on, just reskinned. It also enjoys the typically difficult to explain (see below) but in practice rather unimaginative selection of bonuses.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
There is a basic Wild symbol which substitutes for all other symbols except for the Scatter and Bonus symbols.
Hitting three Bonus symbols in the main game triggers one of the progressive Major, Minor, or Mini Bonus payout. Naturally, these bonuses are weighted heavily towards the lowest ones. Additionally, the number of Bonus symbols is proportional to the size of your bet. So a player risking the maximum £/$/€40.00 per spin will hit the Bonus symbols much more often than someone playing for a lower amount.
Hitting six or more Scatters triggers the Big Hit feature. Paytable payouts are not given out during the Big Hit feature. Instead, you receive three respins during which Free Spins and Random Payouts are earned. After the respins run out these Free Spins play out and the Random Payouts are awarded.
The sequence for the Big Hit is as follows: the three respins are awarded; an amount between one and two times the number of Scatters is added to the Free Spin meter; the Scatter stick in place while the respins play out; if additional Scatters are hit, the respins reset to three; all Scatters are awarded a value between 1 and 50 which is multiplied by your bet per line and added to the Win meter. When there are no respins left, the game ends the Win meter pays out and the Free Spins are triggered.
During Free Spins a new set of payouts are in place. In particular, the Princess Bonus symbol is added to the middle three reels. Hitting four or five of these will win the Mini bonus, six or seven the Minor, and eight or nine the Major bonus.
There is also the Extra Bonus which is triggered randomly in the main game and consists of the Big Hit Feature with the middle three reels covered with a three-by-three Scatter that counts towards any totals.
If the player hits 15 Scatters during the Big Hit or Extra Bonus features, the player wins the Grand bonus.

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The abysmally low return to player on this game 94.31% is much too low for a recommendation, especially when coupled with Enchanted Eyes medium volatility. We aim to only recommend higher volatility slots unless there are mitigating factors. This is because higher volatility slots pair better with our favoured strategies.
The site we tested offered a bet size ranging from a minimum bet per spin of £/$/€0.50 to a maximum bet per spin of £/$/€40.00. Like many Ainsworth games this bet range is rather low, but your mileage may vary on other sites.

media.caption: Paytable for high paying symbols

Conclusion.text:
Despite its complex bonus system, Enchanted eyes is a dull game in terms of its actual gameplay. Coupled with weak design, ugly visuals and a much to high vig.
There is very little to recommend such a slot.

Hitting six or more of the Diamond symbol will get you a go on the Golden Cash Feature. This feature nets you three free spins, which reset to three every time you hit another Diamond symbol.
You don’t win for combinations during the Golden Cash feature but when the feature ends every Diamond symbol nets you between one and fifty times your bet per spin.
The Free Game symbol triggers 8 free spins when you hit three symbols on one spin. During the free spins the ‘1 Free Game’ symbol is added to the reels and will add a spin to your counter every time one lands anywhere on a reel.
The Coin symbols all trigger a mini, minor, or major bonus when they land.
The Extra Bonus Golden Cash feature is triggered randomly and plays similarly to Golden Cash. The major difference is that you start with the middle three reels entirely turned to diamonds. If you fill all the spots with Diamonds during this feature you win the Grand Prize jackpot.

The return to player of this game is 94.34%, rather lower than the yardstick we use of 96%. This is a significant detriment to the game and means the game would need to be pulling a lot of weight to still get a recommendation.
The site we tested Golden Dollars on offered a range of bets from £/$/€1.00 per spin up to a maximum bet of £/$/€40.00. This is a somewhat narrow range and excludes high rollers and the lowest bankrolled players. However, you may find that your mileage varies depending on what sites you play on.

Conclusion.text: Golden Dollars is a somewhat flat experience. Though not bad by most measures (it does have a rather low return to player) it fails to excite with its relentlessly pedestrial creative choices.

Theme and Storyline.text:
The Aztec civilisation existed in Central America across a period that more or less covers the end of the High Middle Ages in Europe. For about two hundred and fifty years between about 1300 and the arrival of Spanish immigrants in the early-1500s their towering pyramids were the great architectural creations of the New World.
But what if they had invented a slot machine?
That is the bold alternative history proposed in Aztec Adventure by BF Games. A strange idol, possessed with fire energy holds out a cylinder of stone to you on which three rows of three symbols are revealed. Press a button and the idol spins the cylinder to make a simple three by three slot.
So now we know.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are really where Aztec Adventure wears its colours. The gameplay is deliberately simple to allow for the greatest possible quality in the presentation.
And at that level it works. The three dimensional animation is beautifully rendered and the whole thing looks as good on a laptop screen or mobile phone as on something larger (sometimes a problem with very high-def slots).
The animations for the reel spins are both fun and varied with the idol spinning the reels with various gestures that really give the game a sense of character and a unique atmosphere. In particular, the way the idol moves to display the wins is something that really uses the 3d graphics to their full potential.
That atmosphere is hugely enhanced by the background audio of jungle noises and the pan pipe musical track, but also by the other sound effects: the rumble of the stones as they spin, the odd chanting of the idol, it all adds up to something that feels about as immersive as a slot machine can possibly be.

media.caption: Win in the base game

Gameplay.text:
The gameplay for this game is solid. A clear effort has been made not to overcomplicate the gameplay in order to allow the animation and programming teams to go to town on the visuals. The result is a game that does not do a huge amount but does all of it well.
As a result, what you get is a three by three slot with twenty seven win ways. Twenty seven win ways is most easily described as any three symbol combo with one symbol on each reel.
The four lowest paying symbols are stacked and pay out triple per line if you fill all nine available spots on the reels with the same symbol.
There is also a simple double or nothing gamble feature which can be used to bump up Aztec Adventure’s volatility and some basic special symbols described below.

media.caption: Gameplay video featuring free spins bonus

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
There is a Wild symbol which substitutes for any other symbol except for the Scatter. You can only hit one Wild per reel, but if you hit one on all three reels they will pay out 20 times your bet as well as the various other wins.
The Scatter provides fifteen free games if you land three of them. Like the Wild you can only hit one per reel. You can retrigger the Free Spins.

media.caption: Aztec Adventure features also a gamble function

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.22%, a pretty standard amount for slots in the industry.
The range of bet on the site we tested was $/£/€0.10 to $/£/€50.00 which should cover most people’s bankrolls but might leave a few super high rollers out in the cold. Your mileage may differ depending on what site you use though.
The volatility of this game is medium, and can be boosted through liberal use of the gamble feature. We do prefer the higher variance option as this works best with our slot strategies.

media.caption: Paytable for Aztec Adventure slot machine

Conclusion.text:
Aztec Adventure is a gorgeous looking slot with a lot of character and an immersive atmosphere.
The gameplay is a little simple, but that should not deter you unless you crave the kind of stimulation that complex minigames provide.
The return to player and variance are not great, but well within the bounds of what we are willing to recommend. So the main thing influencing a recommendation is whether the style works for you.

There is also a random bonus which triggers every few spins in the form of a Reel Clone. This works like the Venus Reel clone.
If a Wild lands on the cloned reels it expands vertically and horizontally to block out a square across each of the reels. The expanding wild adds the same size-based multipliers as in the Countdown bonus.

Where win lines or any way wins have worked for most slots The Grand goes with a system of "any connecting bet ways". This means that symbols must run left to right from the leftmost reel, and must connect horizontally or diagonally to the symbols on adjacent reels. The Free Spin Bonus is triggered by the Free Spin symbol. Hitting three or more of these symbols anywhere on the reels in the base game will trigger the Free Spin bonus.

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Bonus symbol.
When the Bonus symbol lands on a reel, it lights that reel up and triggers a counter which records the bet per spin of that round at the top of the newly lit reel. This light stays in place until the Bonus Game is triggered, when all reels reset.
The Bonus Game is triggered when all five reels are lit up. The amount of the free spins and cash prizes are determined by the average of the five counters at the top of each reel.
The Bonus Game opens on a wheel of fortune, which the lemur will spin for you three times. Each spin awards either a multiplier or a number of free spins. At the end of the spins, the multiplier is applied to the counter average and a cash prize of this amount is paid out. If the number of free spins you win on the wheel is higher than zero, then the Free Spin Bonus is triggered.
During the Free Spin Bonus, any winning combination triggers a free respin. The winning symbols are locked in place and the rest of the symbols are respun. This continues until a re-spin adds no new winning symbols then the win amount is calculated.

The return to player of this game is 95.06%, this is substantially below our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.25 up to a maximum of $/£/€250.00 per spin, which is not a bad spread, though it may exclude some of the more penny-wise players.
The volatility of this game is medium, which makes it a mostly poor match for our preferred slot machine strategies, which tend to target high volatility slots.

Conclusion.text:
The tragically low return to player and high minimum bet make this slot a more expensive prospect than we can recommend. The volatility is not high enough to make up for this, nor is the gameplay or visuals.
On the whole, this one is best packed up in a box and sent back to Madagascar.

title: Wild Heist at Peacock Manor
overview:
Wild Heist at Peacock Manor

about_game: Wild Heist at Peacock Manor takes interesting gameplay and makes it shine even brighter with a fun theme and great art.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Wild Heist as Peacock Manor manages to evoke in one breath the cartoon stylings of Hanna Barbera, the crime literature of the late 1800s (in particular the gentleman thieves Raffles and Moriarty), and the much more recent phenomenon of the comedy heist movie.
We follow a sneaky foursome of no-goods and reprobates as they attempt to steal the golden peacock statue that gives the titular manor house its name.
Along the way, they pick locks, dodge the rozzers, and sneak past thoroughly steam-punk security systems.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Peacock Manor is rendered for us in a truly delightful art style. A kind of children’s book watercolour and ink illustration that feels era-appropriate and lends the game charm.
Unfortunately, like many Thunderkick games, the resolution of the imagery can be rather low which gets in the way of its natural prettiness. This shouldn’t be an issue on a phone screen but on a big desktop might be a dealbreaker for some players.
The music has a similarly nostalgic feel, evoking comedic stealth in the style of The Pink Panther and other comedy capers of the sort.

media.alt: Wild Heist at Peacock Manor mega win
media.caption: Mega win in the Wild Heist at Peacock Manor slot

Gameplay.text:
The gameplay, on the other hand, is almost entirely devoid of character. The base game is a standard five by three slot.
There are seventeen win lines, which is why all wins are relative to the bet per spin, rather than per line. To do otherwise would be to invoke the complications of dividing and multiplying by seventeen.
But what really makes Wild Heist at Peacock manner shine are the various forms of Wild symbol which can be triggered at random during the base game and the bonus free spin game which is designed to result in a different bonus every time you play (see below for details).

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol. During the base game special Wilds can be randomly triggered. These can either make one reel be all Wilds, add up to seven Wilds at random to the reels, or add a Walking Wild which triggers a respin then moves one space to the left. Walking Wild respins continue until the Wild has walked off the reels.
The Scatter symbol serves as a trigger for the bonus. Hitting three gives you a run at the bonus game with three picks. Every Scatter over three you hit gives you an additional pick.
The picks are used in a quick picking game in which a series of face down cards are picked. Each card can give you additional free spins (you start with seven free spins), increased multipliers (you start with a times one multiplier) and a range of cards which add one of the three random Wilds to all your spins.
During the bonus a re-pick can be triggered by hitting two or more additional Scatters.
With the picking game over, the Free Spin bonus begins with the number of free spins, multipliers and additional feature spins that the player won in the picking game.
During the bonus game, the spins have applied to them any Wilds and multipliers that the player won during the picking game.

The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.10 up to a maximum of $/£/€100.00 per spin.

media.alt: Wild Heist at Peacock Manor paytable

Though Wild Heist at Peacock Manor has a volatility of medium and a decidedly average return to player, however the game comes in well above average for style and gameplay.
The world of Peacock Manor is well designed and consistent and the various Wilds and Bonus features make for a varied and exciting game.
There’s plenty here to draw a player into this wild heist.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Thunderkick can so often be relied upon for a slot game title that is insanely specific. Most companies might think it was enough to centre their slot around the abominable snowman, or even around the idea of a yeti battle. Only Thunderkick would get so specific as to name the site of the battle and build their design and world around this.
The result is a slot with real character. We are never given the full story, but it is clear someone at Thunderkick has spent their weekends detailing all the characters and cultures we see in this strange slot.

The green hats of Greenhat Peak appear to be classic Germanic mountaineers complete with lederhosen, buckled hats and comically large moustaches. They are drawn with icicle sharp wit along with their enemies who are among the most adorable yetis in popular culture.
Accompanying these characters are a bright soundtrack and well chosen sound effects and the animations are subtle but effective, underlining each spin and giving the visuals a feel of real weight.
Overall, the front end design is some of Thunderkick’s strongest work.

Into this calming forest the player ventures, hunting for the intricate works of jade art that make up the symbols on the reels. Theme and Storyline.text:
Rocket Fellas Inc. is one of those slots that seems to have been designed by a committee. The title is a pun on the Rockefeller family name – the Rockefellers being one of the richest families in America – while the characters are mining dwarves out of Tolkein but working in a California Gold Rush mine to a soundtrack of 1970s funk. Make of all this, what you can, dear player.
All this mishmash of thematic parts is centred around the rocket mechanic, which does not seem to be best suited to the tight undergrounds spaces of an old fashioned mineshaft. But somehow Rocket Fellas Inc. just about holds together as a slot.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
A large part of what makes this slot work is the design elements. The style is deliberately cartoonish with brightly coloured precious stones and still more brightly coloured beards on the various dwarves.
The animations are bombastic and, in the case of the rockets, explosive. They match well with the sound effects and reel noises.
Even the strange funk track doesn’t feel completely out of place in this brightly coloured world.

Gameplay.text:
The base game of Rocket Fellas Inc. is played on a five reel, four row slot. Although the bonus game is just a free spin feature, the base game remains interesting thanks to the variety provided by several game features. These are triggered by the various special symbols described in detail below.
The spicey gameplay combines with the light hearted tone to keep the player interested.

media.caption: Gameplay video featuring free spins bonus

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol, the Barrel symbol, or the Rocket Symbol.
In the base game, the Rocket symbol can appear on the left hand reel and turns into a Wild symbol. If there is a barrel on the same row as the Rocket symbol, the Rocket will also transform the barrel into a Wild along with any other barrel symbols that are directly connected to it by other barrels both vertically or horizontally.
If a Barrel symbol appears without a Rocket, it can pay out like any other symbol.
Three or more Scatter symbols anywhere on the reels will trigger the Bonus game. The player receives ten free spins for three Scatters and five additional free spins for each additional Scatter.
During the Bonus game, the Scatter can add spins to your total. Hitting two Scatters in one spin will add three spins to the player’s total, while hitting more than two will add the same number of spins as in the base game.
An additional twist during the Bonus game is that any Barrel on the same row as a rocket will be turned into a Sticky Wild and will remain in place until the end of the Bonus game.

media.caption: Big win in the Rocket Fellas Inc. slot

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
Rocket Fellas Inc. has a return to player of 96.10%. This is close to our yardstick for average of roughly 96% and so gives the game a pass mark.
One of the Rocket Fellas Inc.’s major sources of appeal is its high volatility, which makes it a great match for our preferred slot machine strategies.
Unfortunately, there is no system for reducing the number of win lines played from the standard setting of thirty. This limits the player’s control over how volatile the game is.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.10 up to a maximum of $/£/€100.00 per spin.

media.caption: Full paytable of the Rocket Fellas Inc. slot machine

Conclusion.text:
Rocket Fellas Inc. is a bizarre slot in many ways, but under its odd surface lies a solid slot machine with all the fundamentals in place and a few additional twists.
The Rocket symbol adds a fun mechanic that is both visually stimulating and excellent for keeping the game interesting in the slow patches created by the high volatility.
The decent return to player is coupled with a high volatility which should appeal to the strategists in our readership.
Overall, we recommend this slot heartily.

title: Book of Dead
overview:
Book of Dead
    
        Play Book of Dead demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Popular for a reason, this slot steals from a classic, keeping what was good and polishing it until it shines like the back of a scarab beetle.

Theme and Storyline.text:
In this incarnation of the endless Book of Ra imitations, the player is presented with a main character who is no longer a copyright dodging rip off of movie hero Indiana Jones. Instead, the hero, Rich Wilde, is a rip off of computer game hero Nathan Drake.
Beyond that, the formula is much the same – Ancient Egyptian grave setting, hieroglyphics and sarcophaguses on the reels – with updated graphics and bit more gloss on everything. If you have enjoyed the Book of Ra slot and its many imitators before, then you will find nothing to surprise you in Book of Dead.

media.alt: Book of Dead base game win
media.caption: Win in the base game of Book of Dead slot

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are more or less the same as the older games, with a higher resolution and a bit more polish on the artwork being the main upgrades.
The sound effects and music have also been lifted from the old Play’n’Go standard skin, but given a little upgrade in sound quality and complexity. The music does a fair job of setting up a desert atmosphere for the player, but very little else is as well-tailored in the sound effects.
The animations are serviceable, but again are the generic Play’n’Go animations with only the font changed. They lack the Egyptian or adventure movie flare that would hold the game together.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Gameplay.text:
Book of Dead has a base game and a free spin bonus. Both are played on a five reel slot with three rows and ten configurable win lines. You can set the game to any number between 1 and all 10 lines.
The base game has very few other features, but does sport a gamble feature for those who want to crank the volatility of this slot up even further.
Overall, Book of Dead feels like a very standard slot, not doing a lot of different things but doing what it does competently.

media.caption: Gamble function offers a chance to upgrade the volatility

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
Among all the hieroglyphs on the reels, one stands out as special: the Book symbols acts as both a wild symbol and as a scatter.
As a wild, the Book symbol substitutes for all other symbols. While as a scatter, the Book symbol pays out from anywhere on the reels, regardless of whether it is on a winline or not.
Three Books will pay out twice your bet per spin, four will pay out twenty times your bet per spin, and five symbols gets you two hundred times your bet per spin. This is on top of any winlines it is part of as a Wild.
Three or more Books will also trigger ten free spins. During the free spins, a symbol is chosen to expand on any reel where it will result in an additional win. While regular symbols must run left to right starting from reel one, the expanding symbol can appear anywhere on a win line to produce a win.
Free spins can be retriggered by hitting three or more Scatters during the free spins, effectively adding another ten spins to your remaining spin counter.

media.alt: Book of Dead special expanding symbol
media.caption: Special expanding symbol is randomly selected before you start the free spins bonus game

media.alt: Book of Dead big win in one spin
media.caption: When one single spin changes your free spins bonus game

media.alt: Book of Dead free spins big win
media.caption: Then you'll win big after the feature ends...

media.alt: Book of Dead gamble function maxed-out
media.caption: ...and then max-out gamble feature with a few lucky picks

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.21%. This is within the bracket of roughly 96% that we use as our yardstick for average.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.01 if you play just one line or $/£/€0.10 if you play all ten. The maximum bet on the site we tested was $/£/€100.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is as great as the pyramids at Giza; Play’n’GO rate it as 10/10 the highest level of volatility they produce. This ultra-high volatility makes this slot an excellent match for our preferred slot machine strategies.

media.alt: Book of Dead top symbols paytable
media.caption: Top symbols paytable for Book of Dead slot machine, in coin values

Conclusion.text:
Book of Dead is one of the most popular slots out there. This is largely because it evokes popular culture figures in a recognisable setting, and does a similar but slicker job than its direct competitor Book of Ra, which is something of a classic.
On top of these solid fundamentals, we like it for its high volatility and decent return to player. Both features make it a good match for our slot strategies.
We strongly recommend this one.
